divs: sighting detailsiu was walking my dog at 7:28 pm tonite i saw one object moving ...... south western on maybe a 55 degree elevation ,guestimation,. the object was visible several seconds i have been in communication with *(name deleted--cms\sg) i called him was telling him i've had another sighting ,when i saw two more they were stationary and started moving slowly in opposit directions one moved off south western like the first one... the the other two moved in sync with eachother 2nd one was traveling east\south eastern the other was also they were about a twofoot apart from eachother and they were evenly spaced apart like a sighting i had last friday 6 days ago.i just get the feeling to look sometimes ,and they are there.i think atotal of 4 ,but possibly one mayhave reversed course and joined the others the two did not move until the other was in a triangle formation then the others moved from a stationary hover,, the whole time i had awitness,*(name deleted--cms\sg) head investigator of this chapter of this site. the event lasted a total of about 5 minutes...... my watch was dead i had to tap it to make it work again,weird.i replaced battery a few months ago\lithium battery,and i didnt know it wasnt working until several minutes later. the light or glow was maybe a white yellow red hue to it. never blicked or strobed and was up very high they have to be above atmosphere ,i just feel thats accurate they resemble stars the others were in perfect camoflauge not moving obvious extra terrestrials in my opinion,and would challange those who would try to dismiss it as conventional aircraft. erratic darting and curving to right slightly in a lateral line acroos the horizion sky.
